FT  19 JAN 94 / International Company News: Sun Micro surges 80%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Sun Microsystems, the US market leader in computer workstations, yesterday
reported an 80 per cent rise in second-quarter net income.
The company made Dollars 43.8m, or 46 cents a share, up from Dollars 24.1m,
or 23 cents, a year before, on revenues up 8 per cent at Dollars 1.13bn. The
earnings were broadly in line with market expectations.
Mr Kevin Melia, chief financial officer, said: 'Sun's successful new product
offerings and the resulting strength in the high-end product mix, as well as
our continued focus on cost management, helped increase gross margins from
last year's level.'
For the six months, Sun reported net income of Dollars 60.4m, or 62 cents a
share, up from Dollars 28.9m, or 28 cents, on revenues 10 per cent higher at
Dollars 2.09bn.
