<DATELINE>
   ZURICH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
BB Biotech, a Swiss bio-technology investment fund launched last November,
is raising SFr170m (Dollars 114m) in a warrant rights issue.
Mr Martin Bisang, a director of Bank am Bellevue in Zurich which manages the
fund, said the issue was in response to strong demand for the fund's shares.
At yesterday's close of SFr2,830, the shares were at a 7 per cent premium to
net asset value.
