<HEADLINE>
FT  19 JAN 94 / Observer: Marching orders
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Amid the claims pouring in from stricken Californian residents following
Monday's quake, Lloyd's syndicate Barder &amp; Marsh stumbled across a shopping
list from one US name, detailing losses of Dollars 30,000. Appended to the
fax was a request for his London friends to hurry along to Michael Sutty in
Burlington Arcade and replace his bone china military band.
Sutty, whose clients include Lady Thatcher, is the only place in the world
where you can buy perfectly accurate, hand-made bone china replicas of
military figures - which set you back up to Pounds 6,950 apiece. Half its
produce winds up in America but little goes to the West Coast precisely
because of the wobbly nature of the terrain.
