FT  18 JAN 94 / World Trade News: GE contract for turbines
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP-DJ
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
General Electric's Industrial &amp; Power Systems unit said yesterday it had
received a Dollars 12m contract from JGC of Japan to supply three steam
turbines and generators to an oil refinery in Thailand, AP-DJ reports.
GE Industrial said the turbines would drive compressors at the refinery and
the two generators would be used for power generation.
JGC is the engineering procurement and construction supervision company at
the new Star Refinery facility, which is owned jointly by Caltex and the
Petroleum Authority of Thailand.
