<HEADLINE>
FT  18 JAN 94 / World Commodities Prices: Tea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
There was improved demand for landed, with emphasis on better liquoring
teas, reports the Tea Brokers' Association. Coloury Assams sold well,
particularly pd's, but prices were 2 to 6p easier with quality, while plain
sorts were again neglected. Bright and good medium east Africans often
gained several pence but plainer descriptions were irregular and barely
steady. Ceylons met good but selective demand with better sorts firm and
lower quality teas tending easier. Offshore: good general demand. Brighter
teas were firm to dearer but plainer types were sometimes easier.
Quotations: quality 165p/kg, good medium 140p/kg, medium 108p/kg, low medium
90p/kg. The highest price realised this week was 166p/kg for a Rwanda pd.
