<HEADLINE>
FT  18 JAN 94 / Letters to the Editor: More not less in the prize kitty
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr ALAN MCGILL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, I can reassure both Mr I G Baillie and Mr J H Shimmins (Letters,
January 13). There will be no reduction in the number of smaller premium
bond prizes when the Pounds 1m jackpot prize is introduced in April.
The overall size of the prize fund has been increased to accommodate the new
structure for prizes in the Pounds 5,000 to Pounds 1m range. And we will
continue to pay out more than 185,000 of the smaller value prizes of Pounds
50, Pounds 100, Pounds 500 and Pounds 1,000.
So the chances of winning have not become more remote as Mr Shimmins
suggests. The odds of any single Pounds 1 bond winning a prize in any
monthly draw remain unchanged at 15,000 to one, but there will be more money
to be won.
Alan McGill,
controller,
premium bond office,
National Savings,
Blackpool FY3 9YP
</TEXT>
