FT  18 JAN 94 / People: Finance moves - J Henry Schroder Wagg &amp; Co
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Michael Templeman has switched from gamekeeper to poacher in his new role as
director responsible for group taxation at J Henry Schroder Wagg &amp; Co.
Templeman was until the end of last year an under-secretary at the Inland
Revenue, most recently in charge of the Financial Institutions Division.
He joined Schroder as a director at the start of January, and replaces Eric
Henbrey, who will retire in June as head of the tax department.
Henbrey himself joined Schroder from a job as an inspector of taxes in 1966,
at which time he says there was just a 'trickle' of Revenue staff moving
into the private sector.
